    <text id="F8572T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>D. Mittlecoff requests that Edward McPherson endorse George W. Hines for
                    appointment as the Commissioner of the General Land Office.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Honorable">Hon</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Edward">E.</abbr> McPherson</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1860-12-10">Dec 10. 1860</date>
                        <name type="place">Shippensburg</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute><abbr expan="Dear">D</abbr> Sir</salute>
                </opener>


                <p>My friend <abbr expan="George">Geo</abbr> W. Hines <abbr expan="Esquire"
                    >Esq.</abbr> of Cumberland <abbr expan="County">Co.</abbr> will be an applicant
                    for the appointment of Commisioner of the General Land Office. He is a practical
                    Surveyor, familiar with the business appertaining to the public lands. And I
                    think eminently qualified for the place. I understand that his pretensions will
                    be <orig reg="endorsed">endors'd</orig> by <abbr expan="General">Gen</abbr>
                    Cameron, <orig reg="Mr.">Mr</orig> Stevens, Judge Watts, and others prominent in
                    the Republican party.</p>

                <p>I will esteem it a favor, if you can see your way clear to say a word in his
                    behalf at the proper time.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Respectfully truly <abbr expan="yours">yrs</abbr></salute>
                    <signed>D. Mittlecoff</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
